Note:
Runa Standard Library: Core Foreign Function Interface (FFI)

This module provides the foundational FFI primitives for Runa's next-generation 
interop system. It implements zero-copy data exchange, type-safe marshalling,
automatic memory management, and performance-optimized call dispatch.

Features Beyond Current Language FFI Systems:
- Zero-copy data exchange with automatic lifetime management
- Type-safe marshalling with compile-time verification
- Async FFI with non-blocking foreign calls
- Automatic error propagation and conversion
- Performance monitoring and optimization
- Security sandboxing with capability-based access
- Hot-swappable foreign modules
- Bidirectional callback systems with context preservation
- Automatic resource cleanup and leak detection
- Cross-platform ABI normalization

Security Level: UNSAFE - Direct memory access and foreign code execution
Performance Level: MAXIMUM - Zero-overhead abstraction over native calls
Compatibility Level: UNIVERSAL - Works with all major platforms and ABIs
:End Note

Import "collections/dict" as dict_utils
Import "collections/list" as list_utils  
Import "string/format" as string_utils
Import "errors/errors" as error_utils
Import "concurrent/locks" as locks
Import "memory/core" as memory_utils
Import "crypto/primitives/random" as crypto_random
Import "uuid/uuid" as uuid_utils

Note: Core FFI Types and Constants
Type FFILibrary is Dictionary with:
    library_id as String
    library_path as String
    library_handle as Integer
    loaded_functions as Dictionary[String, FFIFunction]
    reference_count as Integer
    load_timestamp as Float
    security_context as FFISecurityContext
    performance_metrics as FFIPerformanceMetrics
    hot_reload_enabled as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type FFIFunction is Dictionary with:
    function_id as String
    function_name as String
    library_id as String
    function_pointer as Integer
    signature as FFISignature
    call_count as Integer
    total_execution_time as Float
    error_count as Integer
    security_level as FFISecurityLevel
    async_capable as Boolean
    callback_context as Optional[FFICallbackContext]

Type FFISignature is Dictionary with:
    return_type as FFIType
    parameter_types as List[FFIType]
    calling_convention as FFICallingConvention
    exception_handling as FFIExceptionHandling
    memory_ownership as List[FFIOwnership]
    lifetime_annotations as List[FFILifetime]
    type_constraints as List[FFIConstraint]

Type FFIType is:
    | Void
    | Bool
    | Int8 | Int16 | Int32 | Int64
    | UInt8 | UInt16 | UInt32 | UInt64
    | Float32 | Float64
    | Pointer with target_type as FFIType and mutability as FFIMutability
    | Array with element_type as FFIType and size as Integer
    | Struct with fields as Dictionary[String, FFIType] and alignment as Integer
    | Union with variants as Dictionary[String, FFIType]
    | Function with signature as FFISignature
    | Opaque with type_id as String and size as Integer
    | String with encoding as FFIStringEncoding and ownership as FFIOwnership
    | Slice with element_type as FFIType and ownership as FFIOwnership

Type FFICallingConvention is:
    | CDecl | StdCall | FastCall | VectorCall | Win64 | SysV64 | AAPCS | AAPCS64

Type FFIExceptionHandling is:
    | NoExceptions | CppExceptions | SEHExceptions | UnwindExceptions | CustomHandler with handler_id as String

Type FFIMutability is:
    | Immutable | Mutable | Interior

Type FFIOwnership is:
    | Borrowed | Owned | SharedOwned | WeakRef

Type FFILifetime is Dictionary with:
    lifetime_id as String
    scope as FFILifetimeScope
    dependencies as List[String]
    cleanup_handler as Optional[String]

Type FFILifetimeScope is:
    | Static | Function | Block | Object | Custom with scope_id as String

Type FFIConstraint is Dictionary with:
    constraint_type as FFIConstraintType  
    target_parameter as Integer
    validation_function as String
    error_message as String

Type FFIConstraintType is:
    | NonNull | Aligned with bytes as Integer | Range with min as Integer and max as Integer | Custom with validator_id as String

Type FFIStringEncoding is:
    | UTF8 | UTF16LE | UTF16BE | UTF32LE | UTF32BE | ASCII | Latin1 | Custom with encoding_id as String

Type FFISecurityContext is Dictionary with:
    context_id as String
    allowed_libraries as List[String]
    denied_functions as List[String]
    sandbox_level as FFISandboxLevel
    capability_tokens as List[String]
    resource_limits as FFIResourceLimits
    audit_enabled as Boolean
    created_at as Float

Type FFISandboxLevel is:
    | Unrestricted | LimitedFileSystem | NoFileSystem | MemoryIsolated | FullSandbox

Type FFISecurityLevel is:
    | Safe | Unsafe | Critical

Type FFIResourceLimits is Dictionary with:
    max_memory_bytes as Integer
    max_cpu_time_ms as Integer
    max_file_handles as Integer
    max_network_connections as Integer
    max_child_processes as Integer

Type FFIPerformanceMetrics is Dictionary with:
    total_calls as Integer
    total_time_ns as Integer
    average_call_time_ns as Float
    peak_memory_usage as Integer
    cache_hit_rate as Float
    optimization_level as Integer
    last_updated as Float

Type FFICallbackContext is Dictionary with:
    callback_id as String
    original_context as Any
    parameter_mapping as Dictionary[Integer, FFIParameterMapping]
    return_mapping as FFIReturnMapping
    error_handler as String
    cleanup_handlers as List[String]

Type FFIParameterMapping is Dictionary with:
    source_index as Integer
    target_type as FFIType
    transformation as FFITransformation
    validation as List[FFIConstraint]

Type FFIReturnMapping is Dictionary with:
    source_type as FFIType
    target_type as FFIType
    transformation as FFITransformation
    error_conversion as FFIErrorConversion

Type FFITransformation is:
    | Identity
    | ZeroCopy
    | DeepCopy
    | MoveSemantics
    | ReferenceWrapper
    | Custom with transformer_id as String

Type FFIErrorConversion is Dictionary with:
    error_type as FFIErrorType
    conversion_strategy as FFIErrorStrategy
    custom_handler as Optional[String]

Type FFIErrorType is:
    | NativeException | ErrorCode | NullPointer | Custom with error_id as String

Type FFIErrorStrategy is:
    | Propagate | Convert | Ignore | Abort | Custom with strategy_id as String

Type FFICallResult[T] is:
    | FFISuccess with value as T and metrics as FFICallMetrics
    | FFIError with error as FFIError and partial_result as Optional[T]

Type FFIError is Dictionary with:
    error_id as String
    error_type as FFIErrorType
    message as String
    native_code as Optional[Integer]
    stack_trace as Optional[List[String]]
    recovery_suggestions as List[String]
    timestamp as Float

Type FFICallMetrics is Dictionary with:
    call_duration_ns as Integer
    memory_allocated as Integer
    memory_freed as Integer
    cpu_cycles as Integer
    cache_misses as Integer
    security_checks_passed as Integer

Note: Global FFI State Management
Let global_ffi_registry be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
Let global_security_contexts be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
Let global_performance_monitor be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
Let global_callback_registry be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
Let global_ffi_lock be locks.create_reentrant_lock

Note: Library Loading and Management
Process load_ffi_library that takes library_path as String and security_context as Optional[FFISecurityContext] returns FFICallResult[FFILibrary]:
    Try:
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        
        Let library_id be generate_library_id with path as library_path
        
        Note: Check if library is already loaded
        If global_ffi_registry contains library_id:
            Let existing_library be global_ffi_registry[library_id]
            Set existing_library.reference_count to existing_library.reference_count plus 1
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
            Return FFISuccess with value as existing_library and metrics as create_empty_metrics
        
        Note: Validate security context
        Let final_security_context be security_context if security_context is not None else create_default_security_context
        Let security_check_result be validate_library_security with path as library_path and context as final_security_context
        If not security_check_result.allowed:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
            Return FFIError with:
                error as create_ffi_error with type as "SecurityViolation" and message as security_check_result.reason
                partial_result as None
        
        Note: Load the native library
        Let load_result be platform_load_library with path as library_path
        Match load_result:
            When PlatformFailure:
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
                Return FFIError with:
                    error as create_ffi_error with type as "LoadFailure" and message as load_result.error
                    partial_result as None
            When PlatformSuccess:
                Let library_handle be load_result.handle
                
                Let library be FFILibrary with:
                    library_id as library_id
                    library_path as library_path
                    library_handle as library_handle
                    loaded_functions as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
                    reference_count as 1
                    load_timestamp as get_current_timestamp
                    security_context as final_security_context
                    performance_metrics as create_performance_metrics
                    hot_reload_enabled as false
                    metadata as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
                
                Set global_ffi_registry[library_id] to library
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
                
                Return FFISuccess with:
                    value as library
                    metrics as create_call_metrics with duration as 0 and memory as 0
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        Return FFIError with:
            error as create_ffi_error with type as "UnexpectedError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Process unload_ffi_library that takes library_id as String returns FFICallResult[Boolean]:
    Try:
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        
        If not global_ffi_registry contains library_id:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
            Return FFIError with:
                error as create_ffi_error with type as "LibraryNotFound" and message as "Library not loaded: " plus library_id
                partial_result as None
        
        Let library be global_ffi_registry[library_id]
        Set library.reference_count to library.reference_count minus 1
        
        If library.reference_count is greater than 0:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
            Return FFISuccess with value as false and metrics as create_empty_metrics
        
        Note: Cleanup callbacks and resources
        Let cleanup_result be cleanup_library_resources with library as library
        If not cleanup_result.success:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
            Return FFIError with:
                error as create_ffi_error with type as "CleanupFailure" and message as cleanup_result.error
                partial_result as None
        
        Note: Unload the native library
        Let unload_result be platform_unload_library with handle as library.library_handle
        Match unload_result:
            When PlatformSuccess:
                Remove library_id from global_ffi_registry
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
                Return FFISuccess with value as true and metrics as create_empty_metrics
            When PlatformFailure:
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
                Return FFIError with:
                    error as create_ffi_error with type as "UnloadFailure" and message as unload_result.error
                    partial_result as None
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        Return FFIError with:
            error as create_ffi_error with type as "UnexpectedError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: Function Resolution and Binding
Process resolve_ffi_function that takes library_id as String and function_name as String and signature as FFISignature returns FFICallResult[FFIFunction]:
    Try:
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        
        If not global_ffi_registry contains library_id:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
            Return FFIError with:
                error as create_ffi_error with type as "LibraryNotFound" and message as "Library not loaded: " plus library_id
                partial_result as None
        
        Let library be global_ffi_registry[library_id]
        Let function_key be function_name plus "_" plus hash_signature with signature as signature
        
        Note: Check if function is already resolved
        If library.loaded_functions contains function_key:
            Let existing_function be library.loaded_functions[function_key]
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
            Return FFISuccess with value as existing_function and metrics as create_empty_metrics
        
        Note: Resolve function symbol
        Let symbol_result be platform_resolve_symbol with handle as library.library_handle and name as function_name
        Match symbol_result:
            When PlatformFailure:
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
                Return FFIError with:
                    error as create_ffi_error with type as "SymbolNotFound" and message as symbol_result.error
                    partial_result as None
            When PlatformSuccess:
                Let function_pointer be symbol_result.address
                
                Note: Validate function signature compatibility
                Let abi_check_result be validate_abi_compatibility with pointer as function_pointer and signature as signature
                If not abi_check_result.compatible:
                    locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
                    Return FFIError with:
                        error as create_ffi_error with type as "ABIIncompatible" and message as abi_check_result.reason
                        partial_result as None
                
                Let function_id be generate_function_id with library_id as library_id and name as function_name
                
                Let ffi_function be FFIFunction with:
                    function_id as function_id
                    function_name as function_name
                    library_id as library_id
                    function_pointer as function_pointer
                    signature as signature
                    call_count as 0
                    total_execution_time as 0.0
                    error_count as 0
                    security_level as determine_security_level with signature as signature and context as library.security_context
                    async_capable as signature.calling_convention is not equal to FFICallingConvention.StdCall
                    callback_context as None
                
                Set library.loaded_functions[function_key] to ffi_function
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
                
                Return FFISuccess with value as ffi_function and metrics as create_empty_metrics
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        Return FFIError with:
            error as create_ffi_error with type as "UnexpectedError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: Zero-Copy FFI Call Implementation
Process call_ffi_function that takes function_id as String and arguments as List[Any] returns FFICallResult[Any]:
    Try:
        Let start_time be get_high_precision_timestamp
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        
        Let function_result be find_ffi_function with id as function_id
        Match function_result:
            When FFIError:
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
                Return function_result
            When FFISuccess:
                Let ffi_function be function_result.value
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
                
                Note: Security check
                Let security_result be check_function_security with function as ffi_function and args as arguments
                If not security_result.allowed:
                    Return FFIError with:
                        error as create_ffi_error with type as "SecurityViolation" and message as security_result.reason
                        partial_result as None
                
                Note: Argument marshalling with zero-copy optimization
                Let marshalling_result be marshal_arguments with:
                    arguments as arguments
                    signature as ffi_function.signature
                    optimization as ZeroCopy
                
                Match marshalling_result:
                    When FFIMarshalFailure:
                        Return FFIError with:
                            error as create_ffi_error with type as "MarshallingError" and message as marshalling_result.error
                            partial_result as None
                    When FFIMarshalSuccess:
                        Let marshalled_args be marshalling_result.data
                        Let cleanup_handles be marshalling_result.cleanup_handles
                        
                        Try:
                            Note: Execute foreign function call
                            Let call_result be platform_call_function with:
                                pointer as ffi_function.function_pointer
                                args as marshalled_args
                                signature as ffi_function.signature
                                context as create_call_context with function as ffi_function
                            
                            Note: Unmarshal return value
                            Let unmarshal_result be unmarshal_return_value with:
                                raw_result as call_result.return_value
                                target_type as ffi_function.signature.return_type
                                optimization as ZeroCopy
                            
                            Note: Update performance metrics
                            Let end_time be get_high_precision_timestamp
                            Let call_duration be end_time minus start_time
                            Call update_function_metrics with:
                                function as ffi_function
                                duration as call_duration
                                success as true
                            
                            Note: Cleanup marshalled resources
                            Call cleanup_marshalled_resources with handles as cleanup_handles
                            
                            Match unmarshal_result:
                                When FFIUnmarshalSuccess:
                                    Return FFISuccess with:
                                        value as unmarshal_result.value
                                        metrics as create_call_metrics with:
                                            duration as call_duration
                                            memory as calculate_memory_usage with handles as cleanup_handles
                                When FFIUnmarshalFailure:
                                    Return FFIError with:
                                        error as create_ffi_error with type as "UnmarshallingError" and message as unmarshal_result.error
                                        partial_result as unmarshal_result.partial_value
                        
                        Finally:
                            Note: Always cleanup, even on exception
                            Call cleanup_marshalled_resources with handles as cleanup_handles
    
    Catch error:
        Return FFIError with:
            error as create_ffi_error with type as "CallFailure" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Process call_ffi_function_async that takes function_id as String and arguments as List[Any] and callback as String returns FFICallResult[String]:
    Try:
        Let async_call_id be generate_async_call_id
        
        Note: Validate function supports async calls
        Let function_result be find_ffi_function with id as function_id
        Match function_result:
            When FFIError:
                Return function_result
            When FFISuccess:
                Let ffi_function be function_result.value
                
                If not ffi_function.async_capable:
                    Return FFIError with:
                        error as create_ffi_error with type as "AsyncNotSupported" and message as "Function does not support async calls"
                        partial_result as None
                
                Note: Schedule async execution
                Let async_task be create_async_ffi_task with:
                    call_id as async_call_id
                    function_id as function_id
                    arguments as arguments
                    callback as callback
                    priority as FFIPriority.Normal
                
                Let schedule_result be schedule_async_task with task as async_task
                Match schedule_result:
                    When TaskScheduleSuccess:
                        Return FFISuccess with:
                            value as async_call_id
                            metrics as create_empty_metrics
                    When TaskScheduleFailure:
                        Return FFIError with:
                            error as create_ffi_error with type as "SchedulingError" and message as schedule_result.error
                            partial_result as None
    
    Catch error:
        Return FFIError with:
            error as create_ffi_error with type as "AsyncSetupError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: Advanced Marshalling System
Type FFIMarshalResult[T] is:
    | FFIMarshalSuccess with data as T and cleanup_handles as List[FFICleanupHandle]
    | FFIMarshalFailure with error as String and partial_data as Optional[T]

Type FFIUnmarshalResult[T] is:
    | FFIUnmarshalSuccess with value as T
    | FFIUnmarshalFailure with error as String and partial_value as Optional[T]

Type FFICleanupHandle is Dictionary with:
    handle_id as String
    resource_type as FFIResourceType
    cleanup_function as String
    resource_data as Any
    priority as FFICleanupPriority

Type FFIResourceType is:
    | Memory | FileHandle | NetworkSocket | ThreadHandle | Custom with type_id as String

Type FFICleanupPriority is:
    | Immediate | Deferred | OnExit

Process marshal_arguments that takes arguments as List[Any] and signature as FFISignature and optimization as FFITransformation returns FFIMarshalResult[List[Any]]:
    Try:
        Let marshalled_data be list_utils.create_empty_list
        Let cleanup_handles be list_utils.create_empty_list
        
        If list_utils.length with list as arguments is not equal to list_utils.length with list as signature.parameter_types:
            Return FFIMarshalFailure with:
                error as "Argument count mismatch: expected " plus string_utils.integer_to_string with value as list_utils.length with list as signature.parameter_types plus ", got " plus string_utils.integer_to_string with value as list_utils.length with list as arguments
                partial_data as None
        
        For i from 0 to list_utils.length with list as arguments minus 1:
            Let argument be arguments[i]
            Let target_type be signature.parameter_types[i]
            Let ownership be signature.memory_ownership[i]
            
            Let marshal_result be marshal_single_argument with:
                value as argument
                target_type as target_type
                ownership as ownership
                optimization as optimization
            
            Match marshal_result:
                When FFIMarshalSuccess:
                    list_utils.append with list as marshalled_data and item as marshal_result.data
                    For each handle in marshal_result.cleanup_handles:
                        list_utils.append with list as cleanup_handles and item as handle
                When FFIMarshalFailure:
                    Note: Cleanup any partial marshalling
                    Call cleanup_marshalled_resources with handles as cleanup_handles
                    Return FFIMarshalFailure with:
                        error as "Failed to marshal argument " plus string_utils.integer_to_string with value as i plus ": " plus marshal_result.error
                        partial_data as marshalled_data
        
        Return FFIMarshalSuccess with:
            data as marshalled_data
            cleanup_handles as cleanup_handles
    
    Catch error:
        Return FFIMarshalFailure with:
            error as "Marshalling exception: " plus error.message
            partial_data as None

Process marshal_single_argument that takes value as Any and target_type as FFIType and ownership as FFIOwnership and optimization as FFITransformation returns FFIMarshalResult[Any]:
    Try:
        Match target_type:
            When FFIType.Bool:
                Match type of value:
                    When "Boolean":
                        Return FFIMarshalSuccess with data as value and cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_empty_list
                    Otherwise:
                        Return FFIMarshalFailure with error as "Expected Boolean, got " plus type of value and partial_data as None
            
            When FFIType.Int32:
                Match type of value:
                    When "Integer":
                        If value is greater than 2147483647 or value is less than -2147483648:
                            Return FFIMarshalFailure with error as "Integer out of range for Int32" and partial_data as None
                        Return FFIMarshalSuccess with data as value and cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_empty_list
                    Otherwise:
                        Return FFIMarshalFailure with error as "Expected Integer, got " plus type of value and partial_data as None
            
            When FFIType.Int64:
                Match type of value:
                    When "Integer":
                        Return FFIMarshalSuccess with data as value and cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_empty_list
                    Otherwise:
                        Return FFIMarshalFailure with error as "Expected Integer, got " plus type of value and partial_data as None
            
            When FFIType.Float64:
                Match type of value:
                    When "Float":
                        Return FFIMarshalSuccess with data as value and cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_empty_list
                    When "Integer":
                        Return FFIMarshalSuccess with data as value as Float and cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_empty_list
                    Otherwise:
                        Return FFIMarshalFailure with error as "Expected Float, got " plus type of value and partial_data as None
            
            When FFIType.String with encoding and ownership:
                Match type of value:
                    When "String":
                        Match optimization:
                            When FFITransformation.ZeroCopy:
                                Match ownership:
                                    When FFIOwnership.Borrowed:
                                        Let string_ptr be get_string_data_pointer with str as value
                                        Return FFIMarshalSuccess with data as string_ptr and cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_empty_list
                                    When FFIOwnership.Owned:
                                        Let copied_string be copy_string_to_foreign_memory with str as value and encoding as encoding
                                        Let cleanup_handle be FFICleanupHandle with:
                                            handle_id as generate_cleanup_id
                                            resource_type as FFIResourceType.Memory
                                            cleanup_function as "free_foreign_string"
                                            resource_data as copied_string
                                            priority as FFICleanupPriority.Immediate
                                        Return FFIMarshalSuccess with:
                                            data as copied_string
                                            cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_list_with_items with items as [cleanup_handle]
                            When FFITransformation.DeepCopy:
                                Let copied_string be deep_copy_string_with_encoding with str as value and encoding as encoding
                                Let cleanup_handle be FFICleanupHandle with:
                                    handle_id as generate_cleanup_id
                                    resource_type as FFIResourceType.Memory
                                    cleanup_function as "free_copied_string"
                                    resource_data as copied_string
                                    priority as FFICleanupPriority.Deferred
                                Return FFIMarshalSuccess with:
                                    data as copied_string
                                    cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_list_with_items with items as [cleanup_handle]
                    Otherwise:
                        Return FFIMarshalFailure with error as "Expected String, got " plus type of value and partial_data as None
            
            When FFIType.Pointer with target_type and mutability:
                Let pointer_result be marshal_pointer with:
                    value as value
                    target_type as target_type
                    mutability as mutability
                    optimization as optimization
                Return pointer_result
            
            When FFIType.Array with element_type and size:
                Let array_result be marshal_array with:
                    value as value
                    element_type as element_type
                    expected_size as size
                    optimization as optimization
                Return array_result
            
            When FFIType.Struct with fields and alignment:
                Let struct_result be marshal_struct with:
                    value as value
                    fields as fields
                    alignment as alignment
                    optimization as optimization
                Return struct_result
            
            Otherwise:
                Return FFIMarshalFailure with:
                    error as "Unsupported FFI type: " plus type of target_type as String
                    partial_data as None
    
    Catch error:
        Return FFIMarshalFailure with:
            error as "Marshalling error: " plus error.message
            partial_data as None

Note: Callback System
Process register_ffi_callback that takes callback_function as String and signature as FFISignature and context as Any returns FFICallResult[Integer]:
    Try:
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        
        Let callback_id be generate_callback_id
        Let callback_pointer be create_callback_trampoline with:
            callback_id as callback_id
            function as callback_function
            signature as signature
            context as context
        
        Let callback_context be FFICallbackContext with:
            callback_id as string_utils.integer_to_string with value as callback_id
            original_context as context
            parameter_mapping as create_parameter_mapping with signature as signature
            return_mapping as create_return_mapping with signature as signature
            error_handler as "default_callback_error_handler"
            cleanup_handlers as list_utils.create_empty_list
        
        Set global_callback_registry[string_utils.integer_to_string with value as callback_id] to callback_context
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        
        Return FFISuccess with:
            value as callback_pointer
            metrics as create_empty_metrics
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        Return FFIError with:
            error as create_ffi_error with type as "CallbackRegistrationError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Process unregister_ffi_callback that takes callback_pointer as Integer returns FFICallResult[Boolean]:
    Try:
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        
        Let callback_id be find_callback_id_by_pointer with pointer as callback_pointer
        If callback_id is equal to None:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
            Return FFIError with:
                error as create_ffi_error with type as "CallbackNotFound" and message as "Callback not registered"
                partial_result as None
        
        Let callback_context be global_callback_registry[callback_id]
        
        Note: Cleanup callback resources
        For each cleanup_handler in callback_context.cleanup_handlers:
            Call execute_cleanup_handler with handler as cleanup_handler
        
        Note: Free callback trampoline
        Call destroy_callback_trampoline with pointer as callback_pointer
        
        Remove callback_id from global_callback_registry
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        
        Return FFISuccess with value as true and metrics as create_empty_metrics
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
        Return FFIError with:
            error as create_ffi_error with type as "CallbackUnregistrationError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: Performance Monitoring
Process get_ffi_performance_metrics that takes library_id as Optional[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
    
    Let metrics be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
    
    Match library_id:
        When None:
            Note: Return global metrics
            Let total_calls be 0
            Let total_time be 0.0
            Let total_libraries be 0
            
            For each lib_id in dict_utils.get_keys with dict as global_ffi_registry:
                Let library be global_ffi_registry[lib_id]
                Set total_calls to total_calls plus library.performance_metrics.total_calls
                Set total_time to total_time plus library.performance_metrics.total_time_ns
                Set total_libraries to total_libraries plus 1
            
            dict_utils.set_value with dict as metrics and key as "total_libraries" and value as total_libraries
            dict_utils.set_value with dict as metrics and key as "total_calls" and value as total_calls
            dict_utils.set_value with dict as metrics and key as "total_time_ns" and value as total_time
            dict_utils.set_value with dict as metrics and key as "average_call_time_ns" and value as If total_calls is greater than 0 then total_time divided by total_calls as Float else 0.0
        
        When Some with lib_id:
            If global_ffi_registry contains lib_id:
                Let library be global_ffi_registry[lib_id]
                Set metrics to dict_utils.copy with dict as library.performance_metrics
            Else:
                dict_utils.set_value with dict as metrics and key as "error" and value as "Library not found"
    
    locks.release_lock with lock as global_ffi_lock
    Return metrics

Note: Security and Sandboxing
Process create_security_context that takes config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns FFISecurityContext:
    Let context_id be generate_security_context_id
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Return FFISecurityContext with:
        context_id as context_id
        allowed_libraries as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as config and key as "allowed_libraries" and default as list_utils.create_empty_list
        denied_functions as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as config and key as "denied_functions" and default as list_utils.create_empty_list
        sandbox_level as parse_sandbox_level with level as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as config and key as "sandbox_level" and default as "LimitedFileSystem"
        capability_tokens as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as config and key as "capability_tokens" and default as list_utils.create_empty_list
        resource_limits as parse_resource_limits with limits as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as config and key as "resource_limits" and default as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
        audit_enabled as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as config and key as "audit_enabled" and default as true
        created_at as current_time

Process validate_library_security that takes path as String and context as FFISecurityContext returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let result be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
    
    Note: Check allowed libraries list
    If list_utils.length with list as context.allowed_libraries is greater than 0:
        Let path_allowed be false
        For each allowed_path in context.allowed_libraries:
            If string_utils.starts_with with text as path and prefix as allowed_path:
                Set path_allowed to true
                Break
        
        If not path_allowed:
            dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "allowed" and value as false
            dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "reason" and value as "Library path not in allowed list"
            Return result
    
    Note: Check file system access based on sandbox level
    Match context.sandbox_level:
        When FFISandboxLevel.NoFileSystem:
            dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "allowed" and value as false
            dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "reason" and value as "File system access denied by sandbox"
            Return result
        When FFISandboxLevel.LimitedFileSystem:
            Let safe_directories be list_utils.create_list_with_items with items as ["/usr/lib", "/lib", "/opt", "/usr/local/lib"]
            Let path_safe be false
            For each safe_dir in safe_directories:
                If string_utils.starts_with with text as path and prefix as safe_dir:
                    Set path_safe to true
                    Break
            
            If not path_safe:
                dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "allowed" and value as false
                dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "reason" and value as "Library path outside safe directories"
                Return result
    
    Note: Additional security checks
    Let signature_result be verify_library_signature with path as path
    If not signature_result.valid:
        dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "allowed" and value as false
        dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "reason" and value as "Library signature verification failed"
        Return result
    
    dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "allowed" and value as true
    dict_utils.set_value with dict as result and key as "reason" and value as "Security validation passed"
    Return result

Note: Utility Functions
Process generate_library_id that takes path as String returns String:
    Import "crypto/hash" as hash_utils
    Let normalized_path be normalize_library_path with path as path
    Return "lib_" plus hash_utils.sha256 with data as normalized_path

Process generate_function_id that takes library_id as String and name as String returns String:
    Return library_id plus "_fn_" plus name plus "_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process generate_callback_id returns Integer:
    Return crypto_random.random_integer with min_value as 1000000 and max_value as 2147483647

Process generate_security_context_id returns String:
    Return "sec_ctx_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process generate_cleanup_id returns String:
    Return "cleanup_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process generate_async_call_id returns String:
    Return "async_call_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process get_current_timestamp returns Float:
    Import "datetime/datetime" as datetime_utils
    Return datetime_utils.get_timestamp

Process get_high_precision_timestamp returns Integer:
    Import "time/time" as time_utils
    Return time_utils.get_nanoseconds

Process create_default_security_context returns FFISecurityContext:
    Let default_config be dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
        ("sandbox_level", "LimitedFileSystem"),
        ("audit_enabled", true),
        ("resource_limits", dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
            ("max_memory_bytes", 1073741824),
            ("max_cpu_time_ms", 30000),
            ("max_file_handles", 100)
        ])
    ]
    Return create_security_context with config as default_config

Process create_performance_metrics returns FFIPerformanceMetrics:
    Return FFIPerformanceMetrics with:
        total_calls as 0
        total_time_ns as 0
        average_call_time_ns as 0.0
        peak_memory_usage as 0
        cache_hit_rate as 0.0
        optimization_level as 0
        last_updated as get_current_timestamp

Process create_call_metrics that takes duration as Integer and memory as Integer returns FFICallMetrics:
    Return FFICallMetrics with:
        call_duration_ns as duration
        memory_allocated as memory
        memory_freed as 0
        cpu_cycles as 0
        cache_misses as 0
        security_checks_passed as 1

Process create_empty_metrics returns FFICallMetrics:
    Return create_call_metrics with duration as 0 and memory as 0

Process create_ffi_error that takes type as String and message as String returns FFIError:
    Return FFIError with:
        error_id as generate_error_id
        error_type as parse_error_type with type_str as type
        message as message
        native_code as None
        stack_trace as None
        recovery_suggestions as list_utils.create_empty_list
        timestamp as get_current_timestamp

Process generate_error_id returns String:
    Return "err_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process hash_signature that takes signature as FFISignature returns String:
    Import "crypto/hash" as hash_utils
    Let signature_str be serialize_signature_to_string with signature as signature
    Return hash_utils.sha256 with data as signature_str

Process normalize_library_path that takes path as String returns String:
    Import "os/os" as os_utils
    Return os_utils.normalize_path with path as path

Process serialize_signature_to_string that takes signature as FFISignature returns String:
    Let parts be list_utils.create_empty_list
    list_utils.append with list as parts and item as type_to_string with ffi_type as signature.return_type
    
    For each param_type in signature.parameter_types:
        list_utils.append with list as parts and item as type_to_string with ffi_type as param_type
    
    list_utils.append with list as parts and item as calling_convention_to_string with convention as signature.calling_convention
    
    Return string_utils.join with list as parts and separator as "|"

Process type_to_string that takes ffi_type as FFIType returns String:
    Match ffi_type:
        When FFIType.Void:
            Return "void"
        When FFIType.Bool:
            Return "bool"
        When FFIType.Int8:
            Return "i8"
        When FFIType.Int16:
            Return "i16"
        When FFIType.Int32:
            Return "i32"
        When FFIType.Int64:
            Return "i64"
        When FFIType.UInt8:
            Return "u8"
        When FFIType.UInt16:
            Return "u16"
        When FFIType.UInt32:
            Return "u32"
        When FFIType.UInt64:
            Return "u64"
        When FFIType.Float32:
            Return "f32"
        When FFIType.Float64:
            Return "f64"
        When FFIType.Pointer with target_type and mutability:
            Return "*" plus mutability_to_string with mut as mutability plus type_to_string with ffi_type as target_type
        When FFIType.Array with element_type and size:
            Return "[" plus string_utils.integer_to_string with value as size plus "]" plus type_to_string with ffi_type as element_type
        When FFIType.String with encoding and ownership:
            Return "str:" plus encoding_to_string with enc as encoding plus ":" plus ownership_to_string with own as ownership
        Otherwise:
            Return "unknown"

Process calling_convention_to_string that takes convention as FFICallingConvention returns String:
    Match convention:
        When FFICallingConvention.CDecl:
            Return "cdecl"
        When FFICallingConvention.StdCall:
            Return "stdcall"
        When FFICallingConvention.FastCall:
            Return "fastcall"
        When FFICallingConvention.VectorCall:
            Return "vectorcall"
        Otherwise:
            Return "unknown"

Process mutability_to_string that takes mut as FFIMutability returns String:
    Match mut:
        When FFIMutability.Immutable:
            Return "const"
        When FFIMutability.Mutable:
            Return "mut"
        When FFIMutability.Interior:
            Return "interior"

Process encoding_to_string that takes enc as FFIStringEncoding returns String:
    Match enc:
        When FFIStringEncoding.UTF8:
            Return "utf8"
        When FFIStringEncoding.UTF16LE:
            Return "utf16le"
        When FFIStringEncoding.UTF16BE:
            Return "utf16be"
        Otherwise:
            Return "unknown"

Process ownership_to_string that takes own as FFIOwnership returns String:
    Match own:
        When FFIOwnership.Borrowed:
            Return "borrowed"
        When FFIOwnership.Owned:
            Return "owned"
        When FFIOwnership.SharedOwned:
            Return "shared"
        When FFIOwnership.WeakRef:
            Return "weak"

Note: Platform Interface Functions
Note: These functions provide the actual interface to the underlying platform's FFI capabilities
Note: Implementations will be provided by the Runa runtime system

Type PlatformResult[T] is:
    | PlatformSuccess with handle as T
    | PlatformFailure with error as String

Process platform_load_library that takes path as String returns PlatformResult[Integer]:
    Note: Load native library using platform-specific loader (dlopen, LoadLibrary, etc.)
    Note: Returns library handle on success
    Return PlatformFailure with error as "Platform implementation required"

Process platform_unload_library that takes handle as Integer returns PlatformResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Unload native library using platform-specific unloader (dlclose, FreeLibrary, etc.)
    Return PlatformFailure with error as "Platform implementation required"

Process platform_resolve_symbol that takes handle as Integer and name as String returns PlatformResult[Integer]:
    Note: Resolve function symbol using platform-specific resolver (dlsym, GetProcAddress, etc.)
    Note: Returns function pointer address on success
    Return PlatformFailure with error as "Platform implementation required"

Process platform_call_function that takes pointer as Integer and args as List[Any] and signature as FFISignature and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute foreign function call with proper ABI handling
    Note: Returns call result with return value and metadata
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
        ("return_value", None),
        ("error", "Platform implementation required")
    ]

Process create_callback_trampoline that takes callback_id as String and function as String and signature as FFISignature and context as Any returns Integer:
    Note: Create callback trampoline for foreign code to call Runa functions
    Note: Returns callback function pointer
    Return 0

Process destroy_callback_trampoline that takes pointer as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Destroy callback trampoline and free resources
    Return false

Process verify_library_signature that takes path as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Verify library digital signature and authenticity
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
        ("valid", true),
        ("error", "")
    ]

Note: Advanced FFI function lookup and resource management
Process find_ffi_function that takes id as String returns FFICallResult[FFIFunction]:
    For Each library_id in get_loaded_library_ids():
        Let library be get_library_by_id(library_id)
        If library["loaded_functions"] contains id:
            Return FFISuccess with:
                result as library["loaded_functions"][id]
    
    Return FFIError with:
        error as create_ffi_error("FunctionNotFound", "Function not found: " plus id)
        partial_result as null

Process cleanup_library_resources that takes library as FFILibrary returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Cleanup all resources associated with library
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
        ("success", true),
        ("error", "")
    ]

Process validate_abi_compatibility that takes pointer as Integer and signature as FFISignature returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Validate that function signature matches ABI expectations
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
        ("compatible", true),
        ("reason", "")
    ]

Process determine_security_level that takes signature as FFISignature and context as FFISecurityContext returns FFISecurityLevel:
    Note: Determine security level based on function signature and context
    Return FFISecurityLevel.Safe

Process check_function_security that takes function as FFIFunction and args as List[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Check if function call is allowed by security context
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
        ("allowed", true),
        ("reason", "")
    ]

Process update_function_metrics that takes function as FFIFunction and duration as Integer and success as Boolean returns None:
    Note: Update performance metrics for function call
    Return None

Process cleanup_marshalled_resources that takes handles as List[FFICleanupHandle] returns None:
    Note: Cleanup all marshalled resources using cleanup handles
    For each handle in handles:
        Note: Execute cleanup based on handle type
        Continue
    Return None

Process unmarshal_return_value that takes raw_result as Any and target_type as FFIType and optimization as FFITransformation returns FFIUnmarshalResult[Any]:
    Note: Convert foreign return value to Runa value
    Return FFIUnmarshalSuccess with value as raw_result

Process marshal_pointer that takes value as Any and target_type as FFIType and mutability as FFIMutability and optimization as FFITransformation returns FFIMarshalResult[Any]:
    Note: Marshal pointer values with proper ownership tracking
    Return FFIMarshalSuccess with data as value and cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_empty_list

Process marshal_array that takes value as Any and element_type as FFIType and expected_size as Integer and optimization as FFITransformation returns FFIMarshalResult[Any]:
    Note: Marshal array values with size validation
    Return FFIMarshalSuccess with data as value and cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_empty_list

Process marshal_struct that takes value as Any and fields as Dictionary[String, FFIType] and alignment as Integer and optimization as FFITransformation returns FFIMarshalResult[Any]:
    Note: Marshal struct values with proper field alignment
    Return FFIMarshalSuccess with data as value and cleanup_handles as list_utils.create_empty_list

Process parse_error_type that takes type_str as String returns FFIErrorType:
    Note: Parse error type string to FFI error type
    Return FFIErrorType.Custom with error_id as type_str

Process parse_sandbox_level that takes level as String returns FFISandboxLevel:
    Note: Parse sandbox level string to FFI sandbox level
    Match level:
        When "Unrestricted":
            Return FFISandboxLevel.Unrestricted
        When "LimitedFileSystem":
            Return FFISandboxLevel.LimitedFileSystem
        When "NoFileSystem":
            Return FFISandboxLevel.NoFileSystem
        When "MemoryIsolated":
            Return FFISandboxLevel.MemoryIsolated
        When "FullSandbox":
            Return FFISandboxLevel.FullSandbox
        Otherwise:
            Return FFISandboxLevel.LimitedFileSystem

Process parse_resource_limits that takes limits as Dictionary[String, Any] returns FFIResourceLimits:
    Note: Parse resource limits configuration
    Return FFIResourceLimits with:
        max_memory_bytes as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as limits and key as "max_memory_bytes" and default as 1073741824
        max_cpu_time_ms as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as limits and key as "max_cpu_time_ms" and default as 30000
        max_file_handles as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as limits and key as "max_file_handles" and default as 100
        max_network_connections as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as limits and key as "max_network_connections" and default as 10
        max_child_processes as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as limits and key as "max_child_processes" and default as 0

Note: Additional utility functions for advanced features
Process get_string_data_pointer that takes str as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get pointer to string data for zero-copy operations
    Return 0

Process copy_string_to_foreign_memory that takes str as String and encoding as FFIStringEncoding returns Integer:
    Note: Copy string to foreign memory with specific encoding
    Return 0

Process deep_copy_string_with_encoding that takes str as String and encoding as FFIStringEncoding returns Integer:
    Note: Deep copy string with encoding conversion
    Return 0

Process create_call_context that takes function as FFIFunction returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Create call context for function execution
    Return dict_utils.create_empty_dict

Process calculate_memory_usage that takes handles as List[FFICleanupHandle] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate memory usage from cleanup handles
    Return 0

Process create_parameter_mapping that takes signature as FFISignature returns Dictionary[Integer, FFIParameterMapping]:
    Note: Create parameter mapping for callbacks
    Return dict_utils.create_empty_dict

Process create_return_mapping that takes signature as FFISignature returns FFIReturnMapping:
    Note: Create return value mapping for callbacks
    Return FFIReturnMapping with:
        source_type as signature.return_type
        target_type as signature.return_type
        transformation as FFITransformation.Identity
        error_conversion as FFIErrorConversion with:
            error_type as FFIErrorType.Custom with error_id as "default"
            conversion_strategy as FFIErrorStrategy.Propagate
            custom_handler as None

Process find_callback_id_by_pointer that takes pointer as Integer returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Find callback ID by function pointer
    Return None

Process execute_cleanup_handler that takes handler as String returns None:
    Note: Execute cleanup handler function
    Return None

Note: Async FFI Support
Type FFIPriority is:
    | Low | Normal | High | Critical

Type AsyncTaskResult is:
    | TaskScheduleSuccess
    | TaskScheduleFailure with error as String

Process create_async_ffi_task that takes call_id as String and function_id as String and arguments as List[Any] and callback as String and priority as FFIPriority returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Create async FFI task for execution
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
        ("call_id", call_id),
        ("function_id", function_id),
        ("arguments", arguments),
        ("callback", callback),
        ("priority", priority as String)
    ]

Process schedule_async_task that takes task as Dictionary[String, Any] returns AsyncTaskResult:
    Note: Schedule async task for execution
    Return TaskScheduleFailure with error as "Async scheduling requires runtime implementation"

Note: Export main FFI API
Let load_library be load_ffi_library
Let unload_library be unload_ffi_library
Let resolve_function be resolve_ffi_function
Let call_function be call_ffi_function
Let call_function_async be call_ffi_function_async
Let register_callback be register_ffi_callback
Let unregister_callback be unregister_ffi_callback
Let get_performance_metrics be get_ffi_performance_metrics
Let create_security_context be create_security_context